Run: `cd web && npx tsc --noEmit`
Expected: No errors.

### Step 4: Build check

Run: `cd web && npm run build`
Expected: Build succeeds.

### Step 5: Commit

```bash
git add web/app/globals.css web/app/layout.tsx
git commit -m "feat(web): redesign — global design tokens, Fraunces + DM Sans fonts"
```

## Context

This is Task 2 of 10 in the frontend redesign. We're replacing the default shadcn design tokens and Geist fonts with a custom editorial aesthetic. All subsequent tasks depend on these tokens and fonts being in place.

The color system uses hex values. Key colors: `#fafaf9` (warm white bg), `#16181c` (dark sidebar), `#e8601a` (accent orange), `#e8e8e5` (borders).

Three fonts: Fraunces (display/headings), DM Sans (body), JetBrains Mono (code/versions).

## Before You Begin

If you have questions about the CSS or font setup, ask now. The Fraunces font variable axes (SOFT, WONK) are optional stylistic axes — if they cause issues, you may remove them.

## Your Job

1. Read the current globals.css and layout.tsx
